WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.458 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.458 --> 00:00:34.086 align:middle line:90%


00:00:34.086 --> 00:00:36.062 align:middle line:90%
[VOICES ECHOING]

00:00:36.062 --> 00:00:37.544 align:middle line:90%
>> Why are we here?

00:00:37.544 --> 00:00:38.540 align:middle line:90%
What is my life about?

00:00:38.540 --> 00:00:41.150 align:middle line:90%
Why is there life at all?

00:00:41.150 --> 00:00:45.192 align:middle line:84%
What's going on,
and why am I here?

00:00:45.192 --> 00:00:47.164 align:middle line:90%
[BOOMING]

00:00:47.164 --> 00:00:48.643 align:middle line:90%


00:00:48.643 --> 00:00:50.130 align:middle line:90%
>> What is the real reality?

00:00:50.130 --> 00:00:51.310 align:middle line:90%
>> Where do we come from?

00:00:51.310 --> 00:00:52.530 align:middle line:90%
>> Look at quantum physics.

00:00:52.530 --> 00:00:54.920 align:middle line:90%
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

00:00:54.920 --> 00:01:02.410 align:middle line:90%


00:01:02.410 --> 00:01:04.620 align:middle line:90%
>> Supreme mind.

00:01:04.620 --> 00:01:06.430 align:middle line:90%
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

00:01:06.430 --> 00:01:11.760 align:middle line:90%


00:01:11.760 --> 00:01:15.030 align:middle line:84%
>> The brain does not know the
difference between what it sees

00:01:15.030 --> 00:01:17.032 align:middle line:84%
in its environment
and what it remembers.

00:01:17.032 --> 00:01:18.240 align:middle line:90%
>> We are running a Holodeck.

00:01:18.240 --> 00:01:20.830 align:middle line:90%


00:01:20.830 --> 00:01:23.280 align:middle line:84%
>> Whatever way we observe
the world around us--

00:01:23.280 --> 00:01:26.738 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:26.738 --> 00:01:38.594 align:middle line:90%


00:01:38.594 --> 00:01:41.558 align:middle line:90%
>> Beautiful, clean.

00:01:41.558 --> 00:01:50.144 align:middle line:90%


00:01:50.144 --> 00:01:50.944 align:middle line:90%
Clean.

00:01:50.944 --> 00:02:03.360 align:middle line:90%


00:02:03.360 --> 00:02:06.490 align:middle line:84%
>> The rabbit hole and how deep
and how far we want to go is

00:02:06.490 --> 00:02:09.589 align:middle line:84%
really how far, how much do
you want to discover about

00:02:09.589 --> 00:02:10.389 align:middle line:90%
your true nature?

00:02:10.389 --> 00:02:15.763 align:middle line:90%


00:02:15.763 --> 00:02:18.180 align:middle line:84%
>> Anybody who spends so much
time trying to explain it is

00:02:18.180 --> 00:02:20.460 align:middle line:84%
likely to get lost forever
down the rabbit hole

00:02:20.460 --> 00:02:22.200 align:middle line:90%
of mysteriousness.

00:02:22.200 --> 00:02:25.470 align:middle line:90%
>> What becomes real?

00:02:25.470 --> 00:02:27.540 align:middle line:90%
Is it our body?

00:02:27.540 --> 00:02:30.690 align:middle line:90%
Is it our cumulative genetics?

00:02:30.690 --> 00:02:32.580 align:middle line:90%
Is it how we look?

00:02:32.580 --> 00:02:33.990 align:middle line:90%
Is it how we walk?

00:02:33.990 --> 00:02:38.610 align:middle line:84%
Is it how much we
weigh or don't weigh?

00:02:38.610 --> 00:02:41.070 align:middle line:84%
>> What we're going to do
with that knowledge and how

00:02:41.070 --> 00:02:44.490 align:middle line:84%
we're going to speculate
and examine possibilities

00:02:44.490 --> 00:02:47.550 align:middle line:84%
and potentials to ask the
big questions-- what if?

00:02:47.550 --> 00:02:48.760 align:middle line:90%
What would it be like?

00:02:48.760 --> 00:02:49.860 align:middle line:90%
How would it be?

00:02:49.860 --> 00:02:51.930 align:middle line:84%
The moment we ask
those questions,

00:02:51.930 --> 00:02:54.210 align:middle line:84%
it forces the brain
to begin to fire

00:02:54.210 --> 00:02:56.220 align:middle line:84%
in new sequences
and new patterns.

00:02:56.220 --> 00:02:57.180 align:middle line:90%
It breaks the routine.

00:02:57.180 --> 00:03:00.820 align:middle line:90%


00:03:00.820 --> 00:03:03.570 align:middle line:84%
>> I was basically trying
to find the answers to what

00:03:03.570 --> 00:03:08.430 align:middle line:84%
I've often called those four
great questions that everybody

00:03:08.430 --> 00:03:10.660 align:middle line:84%
faces whether they
realize it or not,

00:03:10.660 --> 00:03:12.990 align:middle line:84%
even the agnostics
and the atheists,

00:03:12.990 --> 00:03:15.520 align:middle line:84%
as well as the
believers and the pious.

00:03:15.520 --> 00:03:19.510 align:middle line:90%
And that is, who are we?

00:03:19.510 --> 00:03:21.530 align:middle line:90%
Where do we come from?

00:03:21.530 --> 00:03:23.140 align:middle line:90%
What should we do?

00:03:23.140 --> 00:03:25.540 align:middle line:90%
And where are we going?

00:03:25.540 --> 00:03:27.820 align:middle line:84%
And if you don't answer
those four great questions,

00:03:27.820 --> 00:03:31.210 align:middle line:84%
obviously your life
is pretty meaningless.

00:03:31.210 --> 00:03:35.900 align:middle line:84%
And many people just stuff
those questions down,

00:03:35.900 --> 00:03:37.870 align:middle line:84%
and they want the
answers made for them,

00:03:37.870 --> 00:03:40.765 align:middle line:84%
or they want
somebody like Jesus,

00:03:40.765 --> 00:03:42.970 align:middle line:84%
or Krishna, or Buddha,
or somebody else

00:03:42.970 --> 00:03:45.400 align:middle line:90%
to do it for them.

00:03:45.400 --> 00:03:46.560 align:middle line:90%
It can't be done.

00:03:46.560 --> 00:03:49.740 align:middle line:84%
It's like wanting someone
to be born for you,

00:03:49.740 --> 00:03:52.420 align:middle line:84%
or to die for you, or to
eat your lunch for you.

00:03:52.420 --> 00:03:54.710 align:middle line:84%
These things are
inescapably personal.

00:03:54.710 --> 00:03:55.510 align:middle line:90%
>> What is truth?

00:03:55.510 --> 00:03:57.310 align:middle line:90%
What is lasting truth?

00:03:57.310 --> 00:03:58.960 align:middle line:90%
What is really important to you?

00:03:58.960 --> 00:04:02.740 align:middle line:84%
>> Questions about whether the
world really looks anything

00:04:02.740 --> 00:04:05.890 align:middle line:84%
like we take it to look or
whether this is just something

00:04:05.890 --> 00:04:08.980 align:middle line:84%
that's radically altered
by being filtered through

00:04:08.980 --> 00:04:13.220 align:middle line:84%
our perspective,
so on and so forth.

00:04:13.220 --> 00:04:15.100 align:middle line:84%
These are questions
which I take it everybody

00:04:15.100 --> 00:04:18.610 align:middle line:90%
has a natural curiosity about.

00:04:18.610 --> 00:04:24.370 align:middle line:84%
These are questions-- these
are the sorts of questions

00:04:24.370 --> 00:04:29.010 align:middle line:84%
that thinking about them is
what makes life interesting.

00:04:29.010 --> 00:04:30.860 align:middle line:84%
>> Physics of mind,
physics of thought.

00:04:30.860 --> 00:04:31.660 align:middle line:90%
What is a thought?

00:04:31.660 --> 00:04:32.620 align:middle line:90%
What's it made of?

00:04:32.620 --> 00:04:33.580 align:middle line:90%
Is it made of anything?

00:04:33.580 --> 00:04:35.540 align:middle line:84%
Does it have its own
independent reality?

00:04:35.540 --> 00:04:37.300 align:middle line:84%
>> So these are the kind of
things that we have to ask

00:04:37.300 --> 00:04:37.600 align:middle line:90%
about.

00:04:37.600 --> 00:04:40.180 align:middle line:84%
These are some of the questions
that quantum physicists

00:04:40.180 --> 00:04:42.580 align:middle line:84%
and so forth are looking at
and some of the questions

00:04:42.580 --> 00:04:44.410 align:middle line:84%
that researchers of
consciousness studies

00:04:44.410 --> 00:04:47.440 align:middle line:84%
are looking at to try
to uncover and unravel

00:04:47.440 --> 00:04:50.230 align:middle line:84%
what is human consciousness
and how we make sense of it.

00:04:50.230 --> 00:04:51.560 align:middle line:90%
>> Why are we here?

00:04:51.560 --> 00:04:53.920 align:middle line:84%
Well, that is the ultimate
question, isn't it?

00:04:53.920 --> 00:04:56.770 align:middle line:84%
By we, I assume you
mean consciousness,

00:04:56.770 --> 00:04:57.820 align:middle line:90%
conscious beings.

00:04:57.820 --> 00:04:59.410 align:middle line:90%
That's we.

00:04:59.410 --> 00:05:00.820 align:middle line:90%
So why is consciousness here?

00:05:00.820 --> 00:05:05.050 align:middle line:84%
>> Do we really think we've used
the mass of our brain power?

00:05:05.050 --> 00:05:08.830 align:middle line:84%
We think we've really reached
the depth of our intelligence?

00:05:08.830 --> 00:05:10.780 align:middle line:90%
That would be an insult to us.

00:05:10.780 --> 00:05:12.400 align:middle line:90%
We're really great beings.

00:05:12.400 --> 00:05:14.540 align:middle line:90%
>> Where do we end?

00:05:14.540 --> 00:05:18.070 align:middle line:84%
Where do we end and the
rest of the world begin?

00:05:18.070 --> 00:05:20.320 align:middle line:90%
How come we are--

00:05:20.320 --> 00:05:24.280 align:middle line:84%
how come we feel separate
when we aren't separate?

00:05:24.280 --> 00:05:26.140 align:middle line:84%
And of course, one
of the big questions

00:05:26.140 --> 00:05:31.870 align:middle line:84%
is, if everything is mutable
and reality isn't set,

00:05:31.870 --> 00:05:35.350 align:middle line:90%
well, how come it feels solid?

00:05:35.350 --> 00:05:38.590 align:middle line:84%
>> The question really is,
what is God doing to make

00:05:38.590 --> 00:05:39.540 align:middle line:90%
a universe?

00:05:39.540 --> 00:05:40.960 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, god.

00:05:40.960 --> 00:05:46.030 align:middle line:84%
When we ask the great
questions, something amazing

00:05:46.030 --> 00:05:46.990 align:middle line:90%
happens in our mind.

00:05:46.990 --> 00:05:50.770 align:middle line:84%
We have to stop the routine
way in which we think.

00:05:50.770 --> 00:05:53.320 align:middle line:84%
We have to stop
allowing the environment

00:05:53.320 --> 00:05:55.060 align:middle line:84%
to turn on the
circuits in our brain

00:05:55.060 --> 00:05:58.780 align:middle line:84%
that cause us to think the
repetitive patterns that we

00:05:58.780 --> 00:06:02.470 align:middle line:84%
are so in the habit of
thinking on a daily basis.

00:06:02.470 --> 00:06:06.000 align:middle line:84%
To ask the great questions
is to be an inspiration.

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:10.094 align:middle line:84%
It's to stop the moving
locomotive of our life.

00:06:10.094 --> 00:06:13.552 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:06:13.552 --> 00:06:36.820 align:middle line:90%


00:06:36.820 --> 00:06:39.953 align:middle line:84%
>> Are all realities
existing simultaneously?

00:06:39.953 --> 00:06:45.880 align:middle line:90%


00:06:45.880 --> 00:06:50.750 align:middle line:84%
Is there a possibility that all
potentials exist side by side?

00:06:50.750 --> 00:06:58.130 align:middle line:90%


00:06:58.130 --> 00:07:01.460 align:middle line:84%
Have you ever seen yourself
through the eyes of someone

00:07:01.460 --> 00:07:02.585 align:middle line:90%
else that you have become--

00:07:02.585 --> 00:07:14.670 align:middle line:90%


00:07:14.670 --> 00:07:17.570 align:middle line:84%
and looked at yourself
through the eyes

00:07:17.570 --> 00:07:19.190 align:middle line:90%
of the ultimate observer?

00:07:19.190 --> 00:07:23.980 align:middle line:90%


00:07:23.980 --> 00:07:26.540 align:middle line:84%
>> So the film asks, how far
down the rabbit hole do you

00:07:26.540 --> 00:07:28.100 align:middle line:90%
want to go?

00:07:28.100 --> 00:07:33.200 align:middle line:84%
Remember that Alice went down
the rabbit hole following

00:07:33.200 --> 00:07:35.900 align:middle line:90%
where she met the Mad Hatter.

00:07:35.900 --> 00:07:38.225 align:middle line:90%
The Hatter was mad.

00:07:38.225 --> 00:07:41.670 align:middle line:84%
Now, hatters became mad
from mercury poisoning.

00:07:41.670 --> 00:07:44.960 align:middle line:84%
And the idea is you want to
get out of the rabbit hole

00:07:44.960 --> 00:07:46.550 align:middle line:90%
after you've gone in.

00:07:46.550 --> 00:07:49.850 align:middle line:84%
So there's two
stages to science.

00:07:49.850 --> 00:07:52.850 align:middle line:84%
There's the crazy part, where
you go down the rabbit hole,

00:07:52.850 --> 00:07:55.130 align:middle line:84%
and then there's
the part where you

00:07:55.130 --> 00:07:58.280 align:middle line:84%
check the craziness
of your ideas

00:07:58.280 --> 00:08:03.500 align:middle line:84%
against a rigorous, strict,
straitjacket-like process.

00:08:03.500 --> 00:08:07.040 align:middle line:84%
>> I think the interesting
thing about science,

00:08:07.040 --> 00:08:09.470 align:middle line:84%
the interesting thing
about physics is that it is

00:08:09.470 --> 00:08:14.690 align:middle line:84%
a genuinely new and novel way
of trying to come to grips with

00:08:14.690 --> 00:08:16.550 align:middle line:90%
the world.

00:08:16.550 --> 00:08:20.030 align:middle line:84%
I think the experimental method
which is important to physics

00:08:20.030 --> 00:08:24.530 align:middle line:84%
is a very different business
from the method of revelation

00:08:24.530 --> 00:08:28.010 align:middle line:84%
or the method of meditation,
or something like that.

00:08:28.010 --> 00:08:34.039 align:middle line:84%
I don't think it's true that,
for example, adherents of, say,

00:08:34.039 --> 00:08:39.950 align:middle line:84%
Buddhism could imagine
changing their beliefs based

00:08:39.950 --> 00:08:42.530 align:middle line:84%
on the outcomes of
some experiments people

00:08:42.530 --> 00:08:43.640 align:middle line:90%
do with electrons.

00:08:43.640 --> 00:08:47.250 align:middle line:90%


00:08:47.250 --> 00:08:50.700 align:middle line:84%
>> Why this apparent rift
between the Church and science

00:08:50.700 --> 00:08:53.990 align:middle line:84%
or between science and
religion emerged today,

00:08:53.990 --> 00:08:57.334 align:middle line:84%
I think the roots of
that are very deep.

00:08:57.334 --> 00:09:01.470 align:middle line:84%
>> Is News Real films
presents exciting news.

00:09:01.470 --> 00:09:03.140 align:middle line:90%
Is the divorce over?

00:09:03.140 --> 00:09:06.990 align:middle line:84%
Are spirit and science
tying the knot once more?

00:09:06.990 --> 00:09:08.850 align:middle line:84%
Are the Church
and the laboratory

00:09:08.850 --> 00:09:10.850 align:middle line:90%
saying the same thing?

00:09:10.850 --> 00:09:12.930 align:middle line:84%
Out of the misty
ages of antiquity,

00:09:12.930 --> 00:09:14.880 align:middle line:84%
the quest for the
divine and the quest

00:09:14.880 --> 00:09:18.510 align:middle line:84%
for knowledge about the
universe marched hand in hand.

00:09:18.510 --> 00:09:21.470 align:middle line:84%
Ancient Sumer-- there
was a god of astronomy,

00:09:21.470 --> 00:09:24.690 align:middle line:84%
a god of horticulture,
a god of irrigation.

00:09:24.690 --> 00:09:27.750 align:middle line:84%
And the temple priests were
the scribes and technologists

00:09:27.750 --> 00:09:30.750 align:middle line:84%
investigating these
fields of knowledge.

00:09:30.750 --> 00:09:33.570 align:middle line:84%
Ancient Greece, philosophers
asking the questions

00:09:33.570 --> 00:09:35.910 align:middle line:84%
of why are we here,
develop the theory

00:09:35.910 --> 00:09:40.080 align:middle line:84%
of the atom, celestial
movements, and human ethics.

00:09:40.080 --> 00:09:42.640 align:middle line:84%
Medieval Europe--
the Western church

00:09:42.640 --> 00:09:45.190 align:middle line:84%
arose to a position
of supreme power.

00:09:45.190 --> 00:09:47.610 align:middle line:84%
Kingmaker, landowner,
and purveyor

00:09:47.610 --> 00:09:50.430 align:middle line:84%
of the truth, the Church
took it upon themselves

00:09:50.430 --> 00:09:52.950 align:middle line:84%
to be the one knower
of everything.

00:09:52.950 --> 00:09:55.380 align:middle line:90%
The dogma was law.

00:09:55.380 --> 00:10:00.300 align:middle line:84%
>> Because it probably goes
back to a conviction that some

00:10:00.300 --> 00:10:03.210 align:middle line:84%
of the books of the scriptures,
like the Book of Genesis which

00:10:03.210 --> 00:10:06.890 align:middle line:84%
deals with beginnings, is
actually telling us about

00:10:06.890 --> 00:10:08.390 align:middle line:90%
the origins of the world.

00:10:08.390 --> 00:10:11.210 align:middle line:84%
Now, in fact, any biblical
scholar will tell you--

00:10:11.210 --> 00:10:13.160 align:middle line:90%
and this is not news--

00:10:13.160 --> 00:10:15.350 align:middle line:84%
that the Book of
Genesis was never

00:10:15.350 --> 00:10:18.530 align:middle line:84%
meant to be about the
origins of the world.

00:10:18.530 --> 00:10:22.430 align:middle line:84%
But many churchmen believed
that in the Book of Genesis

00:10:22.430 --> 00:10:25.070 align:middle line:84%
you had actual
sort of live news,

00:10:25.070 --> 00:10:28.370 align:middle line:84%
like CNN, about the
beginnings of creation.

00:10:28.370 --> 00:10:31.310 align:middle line:10%
And therefore you had many
people down through the ages,

00:10:31.310 --> 00:10:36.200 align:middle line:10%
like the famous Archbishop
James Ussher in Ireland in 1650,

00:10:36.200 --> 00:10:39.500 align:middle line:10%
who calculated all the ages
of the patriarchs back along

00:10:39.500 --> 00:10:42.080 align:middle line:10%
and worked out to
his own satisfaction

00:10:42.080 --> 00:10:45.560 align:middle line:10%
that the creation of the world
occurred in the year 4004

00:10:45.560 --> 00:10:50.010 align:middle line:10%
BC on the 17th of September
at 9 o'clock in the morning.

00:10:50.010 --> 00:10:53.240 align:middle line:10%
>> Yet science had moved forward
and now challenged the dogma

00:10:53.240 --> 00:10:55.730 align:middle line:10%
that the Earth was the
center of the universe.

00:10:55.730 --> 00:10:58.610 align:middle line:10%
Copernicus, Bruno,
and Galileo all

00:10:58.610 --> 00:11:01.380 align:middle line:10%
felt the heavy
hand of the Church.

00:11:01.380 --> 00:11:06.390 align:middle line:84%
The tragedy-- unable to
suppress science anymore,

00:11:06.390 --> 00:11:08.180 align:middle line:84%
the Church and
science divided up

00:11:08.180 --> 00:11:09.860 align:middle line:90%
knowledge and human endeavor.

00:11:09.860 --> 00:11:11.680 align:middle line:90%
Descartes invented dualism.

00:11:11.680 --> 00:11:15.580 align:middle line:10%
The Church had the
unseen, science the seen.

00:11:15.580 --> 00:11:19.400 align:middle line:90%
And materialism was born.

00:11:19.400 --> 00:11:23.270 align:middle line:84%
>> Descartes invented dualism
to avoid the problem between

00:11:23.270 --> 00:11:26.030 align:middle line:90%
the Church and science.

00:11:26.030 --> 00:11:31.460 align:middle line:84%
>> A long time ago, we made
the decision to separate sort

00:11:31.460 --> 00:11:35.550 align:middle line:84%
of spirit from science
and that science--

00:11:35.550 --> 00:11:40.090 align:middle line:84%
and we were in this
low asymmetry state.

00:11:40.090 --> 00:11:44.000 align:middle line:84%
Because there, the
effects of most humans,

00:11:44.000 --> 00:11:46.600 align:middle line:84%
of their consciousness,
is very small.

00:11:46.600 --> 00:11:51.030 align:middle line:84%
And so we were able to
learn how to do science.

00:11:51.030 --> 00:11:53.130 align:middle line:84%
But now we've
learned, and now we

00:11:53.130 --> 00:11:57.990 align:middle line:84%
can take on the richer task
of learning to do science

00:11:57.990 --> 00:12:00.780 align:middle line:84%
when consciousness,
a significant amount

00:12:00.780 --> 00:12:03.650 align:middle line:84%
of consciousness, is
part of the experiment.

00:12:03.650 --> 00:12:05.880 align:middle line:90%
>> And uneasy truths.

00:12:05.880 --> 00:12:07.800 align:middle line:84%
Scientists were no
longer being bound,

00:12:07.800 --> 00:12:10.180 align:middle line:84%
and they reacted
with a vengeance.

00:12:10.180 --> 00:12:13.150 align:middle line:84%
All the unseen is
fantasy, delusion.

00:12:13.150 --> 00:12:15.030 align:middle line:84%
We are strictly little
machines running

00:12:15.030 --> 00:12:17.010 align:middle line:84%
in a predictable machine
universe governed

00:12:17.010 --> 00:12:19.290 align:middle line:90%
by strict, immutable laws.

00:12:19.290 --> 00:12:20.820 align:middle line:90%
The Church pushed back.

00:12:20.820 --> 00:12:24.240 align:middle line:84%
Soulless scientists
were condemned to hell.

00:12:24.240 --> 00:12:30.060 align:middle line:84%
>> Back in the 17th century,
