00:34:51.870 --> 00:34:53.889 align:middle line:84%
So what's going on we
don't know for sure,

00:34:53.889 --> 00:34:55.597 align:middle line:84%
but it seems that
there's a disconnection

00:34:55.597 --> 00:34:57.060 align:middle line:90%
between the secondary and this--

00:34:57.060 --> 00:34:59.350 align:middle line:90%
the final level of processing.

00:34:59.350 --> 00:35:01.050 align:middle line:84%
So we have some
degree of awareness,

00:35:01.050 --> 00:35:03.570 align:middle line:84%
but it's still not really
that clear vivid rendition

00:35:03.570 --> 00:35:04.620 align:middle line:90%
of reality.

00:35:04.620 --> 00:35:06.270 align:middle line:84%
And that doesn't
happen until we get up

00:35:06.270 --> 00:35:09.090 align:middle line:84%
to the final stages of
our processing, which

00:35:09.090 --> 00:35:11.560 align:middle line:84%
is in what's called the
visual association area.

00:35:11.560 --> 00:35:13.230 align:middle line:84%
And when we see
that, this is where

00:35:13.230 --> 00:35:15.450 align:middle line:84%
we would see this very
vivid picture of what

00:35:15.450 --> 00:35:16.590 align:middle line:90%
the world is about.

00:35:16.590 --> 00:35:17.730 align:middle line:90%
We see all the colors.

00:35:17.730 --> 00:35:21.360 align:middle line:84%
We see everything as if we can
perceive it to be very real.

00:35:21.360 --> 00:35:24.750 align:middle line:84%
And not only do we have this
very real perception of it,

00:35:24.750 --> 00:35:26.940 align:middle line:84%
but again these association
areas as they're

00:35:26.940 --> 00:35:29.790 align:middle line:84%
called because they associate
different pieces of information

00:35:29.790 --> 00:35:33.910 align:middle line:84%
across the brain, connect this
picture with memory banks,

00:35:33.910 --> 00:35:36.690 align:middle line:84%
and if this is a
picture of a dog,

00:35:36.690 --> 00:35:39.240 align:middle line:84%
it makes-- we
identify it as a dog.

00:35:39.240 --> 00:35:41.970 align:middle line:84%
We may have an emotional
response to it.

00:35:41.970 --> 00:35:44.460 align:middle line:84%
If we love dogs, then we
have a warm fuzzy feeling.

00:35:44.460 --> 00:35:46.470 align:middle line:84%
And if we don't
like dogs, then we

00:35:46.470 --> 00:35:48.570 align:middle line:84%
may not like this
kind of a picture.

00:35:48.570 --> 00:35:50.720 align:middle line:84%
So it depends on what
you're actually--

00:35:50.720 --> 00:35:53.700 align:middle line:84%
what your experiences have
been and how you ultimately

00:35:53.700 --> 00:35:56.730 align:middle line:84%
process the information
that really does create

00:35:56.730 --> 00:35:58.660 align:middle line:90%
for you your visual world.

00:35:58.660 --> 00:36:00.180 align:middle line:84%
So the brain itself
is really what

00:36:00.180 --> 00:36:02.497 align:middle line:90%
is doing all of your sensing.

00:36:02.497 --> 00:36:04.080 align:middle line:84%
Conversely, the thing
that I've always

00:36:04.080 --> 00:36:06.960 align:middle line:84%
been fascinated about on
just a very simplistic level

00:36:06.960 --> 00:36:08.910 align:middle line:84%
is that when you stub
your toe walking--

00:36:08.910 --> 00:36:11.887 align:middle line:84%
when you bang into
something, your toe hurts.

00:36:11.887 --> 00:36:13.470 align:middle line:84%
But it's really
hurting in your brain,

00:36:13.470 --> 00:36:15.690 align:middle line:84%
and it's your brain that
actually perceives the hurt.

00:36:15.690 --> 00:36:17.670 align:middle line:84%
But you feel it all the
way down in your toe.

00:36:17.670 --> 00:36:20.446 align:middle line:84%
>> The experiment with
the upside down glasses.

00:36:20.446 --> 00:36:23.680 align:middle line:84%
This man Slater
built these glasses

00:36:23.680 --> 00:36:26.170 align:middle line:84%
made of prisms and lenses
so that you saw things

00:36:26.170 --> 00:36:26.970 align:middle line:90%
upside down.

00:36:26.970 --> 00:36:31.020 align:middle line:90%


00:36:31.020 --> 00:36:33.600 align:middle line:84%
And he had a group of
people wear these glasses,

00:36:33.600 --> 00:36:35.770 align:middle line:84%
and he asked them to
sustain wearing them.

00:36:35.770 --> 00:36:37.220 align:middle line:84%
It was very
uncomfortable for them

00:36:37.220 --> 00:36:41.660 align:middle line:84%
because they saw people
walking upside down.

00:36:41.660 --> 00:36:44.930 align:middle line:84%
But if they kept the glasses on,
then after two to three weeks,

00:36:44.930 --> 00:36:47.360 align:middle line:84%
depending upon the individual,
that with the glasses

00:36:47.360 --> 00:36:48.770 align:middle line:90%
on-- flip--

00:36:48.770 --> 00:36:50.540 align:middle line:84%
they saw everything
right side up.

00:36:50.540 --> 00:36:52.790 align:middle line:84%
And if they took the
glasses off at that point--

00:36:52.790 --> 00:36:55.980 align:middle line:84%
flip-- they'd see
things upside down.

00:36:55.980 --> 00:36:58.820 align:middle line:84%
So what happens,
the way I interpret

00:36:58.820 --> 00:37:04.730 align:middle line:84%
that is that the mindset was
so strong that people walk

00:37:04.730 --> 00:37:07.370 align:middle line:84%
right side up, that
with the glasses on,

00:37:07.370 --> 00:37:12.140 align:middle line:84%
that mindset created a force
to cause the neural dendrites

00:37:12.140 --> 00:37:15.920 align:middle line:84%
to grow in such a way as
to create an inversion

00:37:15.920 --> 00:37:18.470 align:middle line:90%
mirror in the brain.

00:37:18.470 --> 00:37:23.120 align:middle line:84%
And then once that hard
wired structure was built

00:37:23.120 --> 00:37:25.250 align:middle line:84%
and you take the
glasses off, now it

00:37:25.250 --> 00:37:31.620 align:middle line:84%
has to dissolve that structure
in order to see things the way

00:37:31.620 --> 00:37:34.257 align:middle line:90%
you expect to see them.

00:37:34.257 --> 00:37:35.590 align:middle line:90%
It's called neural learning now.

00:37:35.590 --> 00:37:37.990 align:middle line:90%
We do it all the time.

00:37:37.990 --> 00:37:39.780 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's
the way it goes.

00:37:39.780 --> 00:37:43.350 align:middle line:84%
The dilemma is people don't
manifest a lot of these things

00:37:43.350 --> 00:37:44.970 align:middle line:90%
because their mindset.

00:37:44.970 --> 00:37:50.560 align:middle line:84%
The mindset of our world says
that we can't do those things.

00:37:50.560 --> 00:37:52.710 align:middle line:90%
Those things aren't real.

00:37:52.710 --> 00:37:55.000 align:middle line:90%